figgy.title: Bulk ingest of Lapidus items is using the directory name as a source metadata identifier when it should be a title

comments.body:
@roelmoon and I are testing.

- double underscore (__): Still ingests as source metadata identifier in bulk ingest
- single dash (-) between NAME and BIB: Still ingests as source metadata identifier in bulk ingest
- nothing between NAME and BIB: Still ingests as source metadata identifier in bulk ingest
- nothing between BIB and NAME:  IT WORKS!  https://figgy.princeton.edu/catalog?utf8=%E2%9C%93&q=4726349Lapidus

Closing ticket, @tpendragon, unless you would prefer to fix this . We can live with the items currently using the directory names as source metadata ids.   The source metadata identifiers are all going to be added by SC folks to the entirety of this collection anyway during their QC, so it does not affect workflows on our end that they are ingested in this way. 

KEL writing to Toya about this.. any Hard drives already sent to PUL we will ingest as is. moving forward we are requesting the new filenaming convention for this project, due to title only ingest need (the MARC records are suppressed by Don and Steve F. for this collection).
@kelea99 If y'all are doing work fine then it's okay. I suspect this will happen at random intervals for anything with an _ in the name though.
Its good to know, though. I will at least get the word out about title only ingest naming conventions.

@eliotjordan asking Colleen B. to rescan this. transferring issue to Microforms colleagues. Actually. I'll talk with Eric and Will about this one.  If we are going to the trouble to rescan, I would prefer to take that time digitizing the actual item versus the film. Standby.
Got the go ahead from Eric.  @roelmoon is contacting AnnaLee to add this to the patron/priority request pipeline w/preservation review for the actual manuscript versus the film.
